result.execSummary:
The defendant Travis M Byczynski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Violate/Harassment Restraining Order, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.125(7).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Travis M Byczynski in court with attorney Ryan Drengler. Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases heard today are 15CM518 and 16CM15.

2:49 p.m.  Court calls case and states the appearances.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Prosecutor states plea agreement.
Attorney for Defendant will reject the recommendations of the State with agreement stated.
Atty Constable indicates that she would request the case be re-scheduled.
Court informs that they can argue the amount of jail and not have to re-schedule.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
15CM518:
Count 1 - No contest

16CM15 (now requesting a Jury Trial):
Count 1 - DRI
Count 2 - No contest

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Defendant indicates that he would like a Jury Trial for 16CM15 on Count 2.
Court will accept the Plea on 15CM518 at this time.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge(s).
Court reads the victim impact statement provided by Audra Byczynski and per the State a copy had been provided to the defense.
Defendant's father is in the courtroom and makes a statement.

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge(s).
Court finds the defendant guilty on Count 1 of 15CM518.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.

Atty Constable makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Drengler makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Defendant does not wish to make a statement prior to sentencing.
